      <th>1</th>
      <td>204</td>
      <td>OK</td>
      <td>Node is configured to return node status</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>2</th>
      <td>403</td>
      <td>Forbidden</td>
      <td>The HCP node status check returns a 403 forbidden message for the following reasons:\nThe system administrator has not enabled node status through the System Management Console.\nThe HCP system does not have a load balancer or the system administrator has not added the load balancer IP address to the Security Console\nAllow list.</td>
    </tr>
